replies.body:
Yep. Although role selection has dramatically cut down on the number of champ select trolls. 

I think we should be able to call moderators to watch the game to police for suspected in game trolling. That way, instead of reporting after a brutal loss and hoping that your report will help, you can get someone to witness the act as it unfolds, and then give the team (minus the troll) a Loss Prevented. In order to counter premades abusing this system to get their friends out of a loss, premade partners would not receive Loss Prevented if it was a premade member that was caught trolling.

I know that this would require A LOT of manpower on Riot's end, but it's not like they have a shortage of money over there...And if they do need a bit of extra cash, they just need make a skin for the OP flavor of the month champ then refuse to nerf it until you milk as much money out of it as you can...o wait...I forgot...{{champion:105}}
